FBIS3-4848 "dreas041_a_94012" FBIS-EAS-94-041 Document Type:Daily Report 2 March 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Japan Foundation Opens Office in Beijing OW0203005494 Tokyo KYODO in English 0020 GMT 2 Mar 94 OW0203005494 Tokyo KYODO Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] Beijing, March 2 KYODO -- Japan Foundation, the public corporation promoting cultural exchange under the jurisdiction of the Foreign Ministry, opened a Beijing liaison office on Monday [28 February]. Chinese Vice Culture Minister Cheng Changben and Japan Foundation head Shinichiro Asao were among those present at an opening ceremony for the office, foundation officials said. The Beijing office aims to promote Sino-Japan cultural exchanges, they said. The foundation maintains a cultural center in Jakarta, cultural institutes in Cologne and Rome, and liaison offices in Bangkok, Kuala Lumpur, London, Los Angeles, Mexico City, New York, Paris, Sao Paulo, Sydney and Toronto.
